Look into your resolv.conf and add to rc.local route to make route to allow dns if needed. Activate ip fowarding and masquerading if wanted:

/sbin/route add -host 8.8.8.8 gw DEFAULTGW
/sbin/iptables -A POSTROUTING -j MASQUERADE -t nat
echo 1 >/proc/sys/net/ipv4/ip_forward
# Or edit /etc/sysctl.conf and reboot

Add to your crontab:

0 * * * * /etc/openvpn/ResolvDns.sh meisterschule.vpn.priv.de DEFAULTGW

Copy vpn.priv.de.conf, ResolvDns.sh and certificates into /etc/openvpn/. Edit /etc/default/openvpn to start vpn on statup. Reboot. Done.
